# 1. VECTOR — THE MOST IMPORTANT STL CONTAINER

# SIMPLE IDEA

A vector is:

# a dynamic array

---

# WHAT IS DYNAMIC?

Normal arrays:

```cpp id="q9m3tb"
int arr[5];
```

have:

```text id="r5v8qc"
fixed size
```

Vectors:

```text id="t2m7wc"
grow automatically
```

---

# WHY VECTORS EXIST

Arrays have major limitations:

* fixed size
* difficult insertion
* poor flexibility

Vectors solve this.

---

# VECTOR MEMORY MODEL

Internally vector uses:

# contiguous memory

similar to arrays.

This gives:

* fast indexing
* cache efficiency
* excellent performance

---

# BASIC VECTOR SYNTAX

```cpp id="v8x1tb"
vector<int> v;
```

Meaning:

```text id="w4m9qc"
dynamic array of integers
```

---

# ADDING ELEMENTS

```cpp id="y6x2tb"
v.push_back(10);
v.push_back(20);
```

---

# VISUAL IDEA

```text id="m3v7wc"
[10][20]
```

---

# ACCESSING ELEMENTS

```cpp id="q8m1tb"
v[0]
v[1]
```

---

# VECTOR INTERNAL GROWTH

Very important systems concept.

When vector becomes full:

1. allocate larger memory
2. copy old elements
3. delete old memory

Usually capacity doubles.

---

# WHY THIS IS POWERFUL

Provides:

```text id="u5m4qc"
amortized O(1) insertion
```

Very important complexity idea.

---

# VECTOR TIME COMPLEXITY

| Operation     | Complexity     |
| ------------- | -------------- |
| push_back     | O(1) amortized |
| indexing      | O(1)           |
| insert middle | O(n)           |
| delete middle | O(n)           |

---

# WHY VECTOR IS SO IMPORTANT

Vectors are used everywhere:

* AI tensors
* dynamic datasets
* graphs
* buffers
* neural network layers

Mastering vector is critical.

---

# 2. PAIR — TWO VALUES TOGETHER

# SIMPLE IDEA

A pair stores:

# two related values together

---

# EXAMPLE

```cpp id="r2x9tb"
pair<int,int> p;
```

---

# WHY PAIRS EXIST

Suppose you want:

```text id="y9m1wc"
(x,y) coordinates
```

Instead of separate arrays:
pair groups them cleanly.

---

# ACCESSING PAIR VALUES

```cpp id="x4m7tb"
p.first
p.second
```

---

# COMPLETE EXAMPLE

```cpp id="t8v3qc"
pair<string,int> student;

student.first = "Paritosh";
student.second = 95;
```

---

# VISUAL IDEA

```text id="p1x6tb"
("Paritosh", 95)
```

---

# WHY PAIRS ARE IMPORTANT

Used heavily in:

* graphs
* BFS/DFS
* coordinates
* maps
* scheduling systems

---

# PAIRS + VECTORS

Very common pattern.

---

# EXAMPLE

```cpp id="m6v2wc"
vector<pair<int,int>> edges;
```

Used heavily in graph algorithms.

