---

# AUTO

Simplifies complex types.

---

# RANGE LOOPS

Simplify iteration syntax.

---

# TOGETHER THEY ENABLE

Modern elegant STL programming.

---

# COMPLETE EXAMPLE

```cpp id="p8m5wc"
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int main() {

    vector<pair<string,int>> students;

    students.push_back({"Paritosh", 95});
    students.push_back({"Rahul", 88});

    for(const auto &s : students) {

        cout << s.first << " ";
        cout << s.second << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

---

# OUTPUT

```text id="x3v7tb"
Paritosh 95
Rahul 88
```

---

# WHY THIS EXAMPLE IMPORTANT

Combines:

* vector
* pair
* auto
* range loops

This style appears everywhere in modern C++.

